ociation%20of%20Realtors%20(NAR).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLess%20trade-dependent%20states%20tend%20to%20have%20more%20diversified%20service-based%20economies%2C%20and%20they've%20added%20jobs%20at%20a%20faster%20pace%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadia%20Evangelou%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20NAR%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20many%20of%20these%20states%2C%20job%20creation%20has%20attracted%20new%20residents%20and%20supported%20steady%20housing%20demand.%20That%20can%20drive%20up%20both%20home%20construction%20and%20price%20appreciation%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Evangelou%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvangelou%20categorizes%20a%20state%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-markets-most-at-risk-trade-war-tariffs-home-values-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade-reliant%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20exports%20account%20for%20more%20than%207%25%20of%20its%20total%20GDP.%20Some%20states%2C%20like%20Louisiana%2C%20have%20over%2025%25%20of%20their%20GDPs%20tied%20up%20in%20exports%20to%20countries%20like%20China%20and%20Mexico.%20On%20the%20opposite%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20only%200.4%25%20of%20Hawaii's%20GDP%20comes%20from%20foreign%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStates%20with%20smaller%20export%20shares%20are%20more%20shielded%20from%20global%20supply%20chain%20disruptions.%20These%20states%20usually%20have%20more%20stable%20job%20markets%20as%20their%20economies%20tend%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20services%20in%20finance%2C%20tourism%2C%20or%20entertainment.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20increases%20housing%20demand%20in%20urban%20and%20suburban%20areas%2C%20Evangelou%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gap%20between%20high%20and%20low%20trade-reliant%20states%20isn't%20just%20present%20in%20times%20of%20economic%20crisis%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0historically%2C%20home%20prices%20have%20appreciated%20faster%20in%20states%20with%20lower%20international%20exposure.%20Over%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20home