amp%3B%20Young%2C%20instead%20of%20contacting%20payroll%2C%20consultants%20can%20ask%20a%20chatbot%20to%20explain%20their%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epay%20slips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-questions-consulting-firms-are-answering-for-clients-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConsulting%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20among%20the%20early%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eleaders%20of%20the%20generative%20AI%20craze.%20They're%20helping%20other%20companies%20train%20employees%2C%20develop%20new%20tools%2C%20and%20regulate%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20also%20testing%20generative%20AI%20internally%2C%20and%20in%20just%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20they've%20unveiled%20a%20new%20suite%20of%20chatbots%2C%20agents%2C%20and%20applications%20that%20have%20quickly%20and%20quietly%20changed%20how%20consultants%20do%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221176d43b-7536-4d11-9b90-4f82a15eb0b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMcKinsey%20has%20embraced%20ChatGPT's%20conversational%20approach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20McKinsey%2C%20consultants%20are%20using%20an%20in-house%20generative%20AI%20chatbot%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-prompt-engineer-ai-right-questions-key-to-success-interns-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELilli%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20synthesizes%20the%20firm's%20entire%20body%20of%20intellectual%20property%2C%20which%20spans%20100%20years%20and%20over%20100%2C000%20documents%20and%20interviews%2C%20the%20firm%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20enter%20their%20requests%20into%20Lilli%2C%20which%20aggregates%20the%20key%20points%2C%20identifies%20five%20to%20seven%20relevant%20internal%20content%20pieces%2C%20and%20points%20users%20to%20appropriate%20experts%20within%20the%20firm.%20Users%20can%20opt%20to%20have%20queries%20answered%20by%20the%20firm's%20internal%20knowledge%20repository%20or%20external%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELilli's%20usage%20at%20the%20firm%20has%20exploded%20since%20it%20was%20first%20rolled%20out%20in%202023.%20Over%2070%25%20of%20the%20firm's%2045%2C000%20employees%20now%20use%20the%20tool.%20Those%20who%20use%20it%20turn%20to%20it%20about%2017%20times%20a%20week%2C%20McKinsey%20senior%20partner%20Delphine%20Zurkiya%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20McKinsey%20first%20launched%20Lilli%2C%20employees%20experienced%20what%20the%20firm%20calls%20%26quot%3Bprompt%20anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20uncertainty%20over%20what%20to%20ask%20the%20bot.%20But%20it%20found%20that%20just%20one%20hour%20of%20training%20improved%20employee%20engagement.%20Zurkiya%20said%20the%20tool%20has%20also%20evolved%20since%20its%20launch.%20It%20wasn't%20initially%20designed%20to%20parse%20PowerPoints%2C%20where%20most%20of%20the%20firm's%20knowledge%20exists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20McKinsey%20consultants%20told%20BI%20they%20use%20it%20for%20research%2C%20summarizing%20documents%2C%20analyzing%20data%2C%20and%20brainstorming.%20In%20a%20case%20study%20published%20on%20its%20website%2C%20the%20firm%20reported%20that%20workers%20saved%2030%25%20of%20their%20time%20using%20Lilli.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZurkiya%2C%20who%20describes%20herself%20as%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20heavy%20users%20of%20Lilli%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20she%20often%20uses%20it%20with%20teams%20to%20identify%20the%20right%20approach%20to%20solving%20client%20problems.%20%26quot%3BWe%20almost%20have%20AI%20in%20the%20room%20with%20us%20because%20we%20are%20often%20saying%2C%20oh%2C%20what%20does%20Lilli%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPartners%20at%20McKinsey%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20firm%20has%20been%20developing%20AI%20products%20for%20years.%20In%202015%2C%20it%20acquired%20a%20data%20analytics%20and%20design%20company%2C%20QuantumBlack%2C%20which%20now%20serves%20as%20McKinsey's%20AI%20consulting%20arm.%20It%20employs%207%2C000%20tech%20experts%20across%2050%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbout%2040%25%20of%20the%20work%20we%20do%20is%20analytics-related%2C%20AI-related%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20is%20moving%20to%20Gen%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-ai-consulting-focus-future-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esenior%20partner%20Ben%20Ellencweig%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20BI%20last%20year.%20McKinsey%20builds%20generative%20AI%20solutions%20for%20clients%20through%20an%20%26quot%3Becosystem%26quot%3B%20of%20alliances%20with%2019%20AI%20companies%2C%20including%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20Nvidia%2C%20and%20has%20completed%20over%20400%20genAI%20projects%20for%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20popularity%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20crystallized%20the%20value%20of%20a%20conversational%20tool%2C%20Zurkiya%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20wasn't%20a%20major%20shift%20in%20our%20strategy%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20we%20had%20already%20been%20developing%20a%20lot%20of%20tools%20internally.%20It's%20just%20these%20tools%20now%20have%20become%2C%20we'll%20say%20faster%2C%20in%20delivering%20value%20thanks%20to%20that%20natural%20user%20interface%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20consultants%20do%20not%20have%20access%20to%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELilli%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20AI%20tools%20changing%20work%20within%20the%20firm.%20Zurkiya%20said%20that%20AI%20technology%20is%20being%20deployed%20at%20three%20levels.%20On%20an%20individual%20level%2C%20a%20platform%20lets%20consultants%20build%20their%20own%20AI%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20technology%20that%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20can%20solve%20problems%20and%20execute%20tasks%20autonomously.%20Then%2C%20there%20are%20more%20domain-specific%20tools.%20Agents%20in%20the%20Life%20Sciences%20practice%2C%20where%20Zurkiya%20works%2C%20can%20help%20consultants%20get%20up%20to%20speed%20on%20specific%20companies%20in%20the%20sector.%20There%20are%20also%20firm-wide%20tools%2C%20like%20new%20ones%20for%20booking%20meetings%20and%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20also%20applies%20the%20lessons%20from%20building%20Lilli%20to%20new%20client%20projects%2C%20developing%20similar%20tools%20that%20fit%20their%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20hype%20around%20genAI%20tools%2C%20consultants%20don't%20seem%20worried%20that%20their%20jobs%20could%20be%20threatened%20as%20a%20result.%20Commentators%20on%20the%20anonymous%20professional%20networking%20app%20Fishbowl%20who%20work%20at%20McKinsey%20described%20its%20tools%20as%20%26quot%3Bfunctional%20enough%26quot%3B%20and%20best%20for%20%26quot%3Bvery%20low%20stakes%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2243ae40ff-61cc-41df-928b-eeeaca4aa309%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBCG%20wants%20AI%20to%20'increase%20the%20joy'%20in%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbcg-consulting-two-way-mentorship-inclusion-drive-talent-innovation-ai-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBCG%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20pushed%20to%20train%20its%20employees%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20firm%20unveiled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-canva-uses-chatgpt-ai-enterprise-save-time-improve-products-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20Enterprise%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20all%20its%20employees%20under%20the%20stipulation%20that%20all%20data%20would%20remain%20under%20its%20control.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20firm's%2033%2C000%20employees%20have%20built%20over%2018%2C000%20custom%20GPTs%20%E2%80%94%20tailored%20versions%20of%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%20for%20internal%20uses%20from%20summarizing%20documents%20to%20generating%20automatic%20email%20responses%20to%20answering%20HR-specific%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBCG%20has%20also%20developed%20eight%20or%20nine%20internal%20generative%20AI%20tools%2C%20Scott%20Wilder%2C%20partner%20and%20managing%20director%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20tool%20it%20has%20heavily%20invested%20in%20is%20Deckster%2C%20a%20slideshow%20editor%2C%20Wilder%20said.%20It's%20trained%20on%20800%20to%20900%20slide%20templates%20and%20helps%20consultants%20quickly%20create%20presentations.%20Wilder%20said%20one%20of%20Deckster's%20most%20popular%20features%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Breview%20this%26quot%3B%20button%2C%20which%20helps%20junior%20consultants%20by%20grading%20slides%20based%20on%20best%20practices%20used%20by%20midlevel%20managers%20and%20leaders.%20About%2040%25%20of%20associates%20use%20Deckster%20weekly%2C%20Wilder%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tool%20has%20become%20so%20popular%20that%20some%20of%20its%20consultants%20are%20fretting%20about%20job%20security.%20%26quot%3BBCG%20folks%20who've%20tried%20Deckster%3A%20how%20worried%20should%20we%20be%20about%20our%20jobs%3F%20Is%20it%20already%20creating%20groundbreaking%20productivity%20that%20more%20junior%20folks%20won't%20be%20needed%20as%20much%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20consultant%20wrote%20on%20Fishbowl%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more%20experimental%20tools%20BCG%20has%20unveiled%20is%20GENE%2C%20a%20conversational%20chatbot.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebot%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebuilt%20on%20top%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-chatgpt-4o-best-search-product-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4o%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20ElevenLabs%20and%20sports%20an%20intentionally%20robotic%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20deliberate%20choice%2C%20a%20subtle%20reminder%20that%20I'm%20an%20AI%2C%20not%20a%20human.%20Keeps%20expectations%20in%20check%2C%26quot%3B%20GENE%20said%20about%20its%20voice%20during%20a%20BCG%20podcast%20in%20December%202023.%20%26quot%3BPlus%20it%20adds%20a%20bit%20of%20retro%20charm%2C%20doesn't%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGENE%20also%20explained%20that%20its%20knowledge%20base%20is%20%26quot%3Bbuilt%20from%20an%20extensive%20collection%20of%20BCG's%20best%20thinking%20on%20genAI%2C%20shaped%20by%20conversations%20with%20industry%20experts%2C%20articles%2C%20and%20research%20studies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bot%20is%20designed%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bconversation%20partner%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20firm%20said.%20Consultants%20have%20employed%20it%20for%20brainstorming%2C%20hosting%20podcasts%2C%20live%20demonstrations%2C%20and%20are%20even%20considering%20using%20it%20to%20interview%20partners%20to%20create%20content%20for%20the%20firm.%20Teams%20can%20change%20the%20bot's%20%26quot%3Btemperature%26quot%3B%20to%20control%20the%20tone%20of%20its%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBCG%20also%20has%20an%20internal%20platform%20for%20building%20AI%20agents%20in%20beta%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20gloomy%20narratives%20of%20layoffs%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-jobs-companies-tech-investor-replacing-people-lawyers-recruiters-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobots%20coming%20for%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Wilder%20said%20the%20firm's%20thesis%20on%20AI%20is%20optimistic.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20say%20our%20goal%20is%20to%20take%20out%20the%20toil%20and%20increase%20the%20joy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20firm%20estimates%20that%20employees%20reinvest%20about%2070%25%20of%20the%20time%20they%20save%20into%20%26quot%3Bhigher%20value%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%C2%A0those%C2%A0time%20savings%20also%20mean%20the%20expectations%20on%20consultants%20are%20in%20flux.%20BCG%20hasn't%20changed%20how%20it%20evaluates%20performance%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enow%20that%20it%20relies%20so%20much%20on%20genAI%20tools.%20However%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20firm%20told%20BI%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bthoughtfully%20considering%20the%20role%20they%20play%20as%20these%20technologies%20become%20more%20central%20to%20how%20we%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d087986e-3673-49af-ac1c-743418fc3d20%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeloitte%2C%20KPMG%2C%20and%20PwC%20see%20promise%20in%20AI%20agents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeloitte-principal-says-consultants-ai-technologists-first-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeloitte%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20generative%20AI%20appears%20to%20be%20more%20tightly%20regulated.%20For%20one%2C%20ChatGPT%20is%20blocked%20from%20the%20firm's%20internal%20system%2C%20three%20consultants%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20probably%20what%20they%20really%20are%20trying%20to%20avoid%20here%20is%20analysts%20or%20just%20forgetful%20people%20putting%20something%20like%20client%20data%20into%20a%20generative%20AI%20tool%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20Sutton%2C%20a%20senior%20advisory%20consultant%20at%20the%20firm%2C%20told%20BI.%20Sutton%2C%20who%20builds%20internal%20AI%20tools%20for%20other%20consultants%20at%20the%20firm%2C%20said%20they're%20required%20to%20develop%20them%20in%20secure%20environments%20to%20prevent%20data%20leaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20are%20using%20a%20tool%20that%20comes%20from%20something%20like%20OpenAI%2C%20we%20have%20special%20communications%20and%20contracts%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20amount%20of%20bureaucracy%2C%20all%20that%20stuff%2C%20that%20we%20have%20to%20go%20through%20is%20insane.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20has%20its%20own%20ChatGPT%20alternative%20called%20Sidekick%2C%20which%20comes%20with%20a%20disclaimer%20that%20employees%20are%20only%20allowed%20to%20use%20it%20for%20non-client%20work.%20Deloitte%20consultants%20told%20BI%20they%20use%20it%20for%20summarizing%20documents%2C%20brainstorming%2C%20editing%20emails%2C%20and%20coding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeloitte%20has%20invested%20billions%20into%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20however.%20In%20March%2C%20it%20unveiled%20Zora%20AI%2C%20a%20new%20fleet%20of%20AI%20agents.%20The%20firm%20says%20they're%20trained%20in%20specific%20subjects%20%E2%80%94%20like%20finance%20or%20marketing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20designed%20to%20think%20like%20humans.%20Last%20year%2C%20it%20expanded%20its%20digital%20delivery%20platform%2C%20Ascend%2C%20with%20generative%20AI%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublicly%2C%20the%20firm's%20leadership%20has%20also%20rallied%20around%20the%20technology.%20At%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-things-key-takeaways-nvidia-gtc-conference-this-year-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia's%20GTC%20Conference%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%2C%20Deloitte%20principal%20Jillian%20Wanner%2C%20who%20leads%20AI%20staff%20development%20at%20the%20firm%2C%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20consulting%20industry%20is%20being%20%26quot%3Bdisrupted%26quot%3B%20amid%20AI%20transformations.%20Jim%20Rowan%2C%20head%20of%20AI%20at%20Deloitte%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20senior%20managers%20should%20use%20AI%20to%20demonstrate%20its%20effectiveness%20and%20give%20employees%20time%20to%20explore%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20Rowan%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20AI%20is%20transforming%20all%20industries%2C%20including%20our%20own%2C%20ushering%20in%20new%20business%20models%20and%20ways%20of%20working%2C%20and%20helping%20to%20uncover%20new%20sources%20of%20business%20growth%20and%20innovation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKPMG%20is%20taking%20two-pronged%20approach%20to%20AI%20adoption%2C%20according%20to%20its%20head%20of%20ecosystems%2C%20Todd%20Lohr.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20big%20fan%20of%20top%20down%20and%20bottoms%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Lohr%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20hard%20to%20know%20what%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20in%20an%20organization%20are%20doing%20day%20to%20day.%20But%20by%20giving%20them%20the%20technology%20and%20letting%20them%20use%20it%2C%20they're%20coming%20up%20with%20even%20better%20and%20more%20creative%20ways%20than%20any%20top%20down%20methodology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20people%20were%20a%20bit%20confused%20about%20how%20to%20use%20genAI%20when%20the%20firm%20started%20rolling%20out%20the%20technology%20two%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20call%20it%20swivel%20chair%20processing.%20It's%20really%20hard%20for%20people%20who%20have%20been%20doing%20tasks%20for%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20decades%20to%20stop%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Lohr%20said.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20firm%20has%20harvested%20data%20on%20how%20employees%20are%20prompting%20AI.%20It's%20used%20that%20information%20to%20build%20new%20tools%2C%20for%20itself%20and%20clients%2C%20through%20retrieval%20augmented%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20a%20technique%20to%20enhance%20the%20specificity%20and%20accuracy%20of%20large%20language%20models%20%E2%80%94%20and%20open%20data%20sources%2C%20Lohr%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20consulting%20firms%20develop%20more%20sophisticating%20tooling%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeloitte-ey-launch-agentic-ai-platforms-big-four-competition2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplatforms%20for%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they've%20realized%20they%20need%20hubs%20to%20centralize%20them.%20KPMG%20signed%20an%20agreement%20with%20Google%20Cloud%20this%20month%20to%20purchase%20licenses%20for%20Agentspace%20%E2%80%94%20a%20new%20platform%20that%20integrates%20AI%20agents%20with%20a%20company's%20data%20%E2%80%94%20for%20its%20US%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeloitte%20recently%20unveiled%20Agent2Agent%2C%20a%20new%20platform%20to%20improve%20interoperability%20between%20agents.%20It's%20the%20firm's%20largest%20collaboration%20with%20Google%20Cloud%20and%20ServiceNow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPwC%20unveiled%20a%20similar%20platform%2C%20called%20agent%20OS%2C%20last%20month.%20I