0in%202025%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20becoming%20a%20harder%20labor%20market%20for%20those%20who%20are%20out%20of%20a%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Stahle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220580b8d1-28ea-4c7e-8ea8-5ff44036c609%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20boost%20if%20your%20network%20is%20small%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDulski%20said%20a%20top-notch%20application%20can%20be%20especially%20helpful%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20much%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-post-help-family-job-search-risks-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional%20network%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20turn%20to%20during%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-workers-tough-job-search-private-sector-roles-layoffs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20search%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20important%20because%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20land%20a%20gig%20has%20long%20been%20to%20tap%20a%20connection%20within%20an%20organization.%20That's%20still%20true%2C%20she%20said.%20While%20it%20won't%20necessarily%20get%20you%20the%20job%2C%20it%20might%20lead%20to%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDulski%2C%20who%20teaches%20at%20the%20Stanford%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20and%20talks%20often%20with%20students%20early%20in%20their%20careers%2C%20still%20recommends%20that%20you%20try%20to%20connect%20with%20someone%20in%20an%20organization%2C%20even%20through%20cold%20outreach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20where%20that%20doesn't%20work%2C%20Dulski%20said%2C%20putting%20added%20effort%20into%20an%20application%20can%20help%20compensate%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20an%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20strategy%20of%20sending%20something%20extra%2C%20making%20yourself%20stand%20out%2C%20is%20accessible%20to%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDulski%20said%20that's%20the%20case%20regardless%20of%20your%20connections%2C%20any%20privileges%20you%20might%20have%2C%20or%20what's%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223dbe9fa4-0b7b-4cda-910c-cde83d61cb41%5C%22%3EThe%20basics%20still%20count%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20research%20an%20employer%20to%20help%20shape%20your%20application%2C%20you%20still%20have%20to%20nail%20the%20basics%2C%20Susan%20Peppercorn%2C%20an%20executive%20coach%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20having%20a%20strong%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20LinkedIn%20profile%20%E2%80%94%20LinkedIn%20is%20the%20first%20place%20a%20hiring%20manager%20will%20go%20to%20look%20you%20up%2C%20Peppercorn%20said.%20With%20something%20like%20your%20profile%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20clear%20what%20you%20want%20to%20say%20about%20yourself%20to%20stand%20out%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20makes%20you%20unique%20and%20compelling%3F%26quot%3B%20Peppercorn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20well-tailored%20application%20along%20with%20a%20strong%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20dialed%20profile%20still%20might%20not%20guarantee%20you%20get%20somewhere%20with%20an%20employer.%20Yet%2C%20Dulski%20said%2C%20given%20the%20number%20of%20applications%20some%20postings%20get%2C%20job%20seekers%20often%20need%20to%20do%20something%20to%20stand%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20she%20said%2C%20a%20well-executed%20application%20can%20help%20you%20show%20off%20your%20skills.%20It's%20also%20a%20help%2C%20Dulski%20said%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20exact%20experience%20listed%20in%20a%20job%20posting.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20person%20Dulski%20hired%20hadn't%20been%20a%20chief%20of%20staff%20before.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20the%20hire%20wasn't%20one%20of%20those%20who%20added%20something%20extra%20to%20their%20application%2C%20Dulski%20shared%20her%20finalists%20with%20other%20business%20leaders%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20several%20applicants%20getting%20interviews%20at%20other%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGreat%20talent%20will%20still%20get%20jobs%2C%20even%20